reviews.reviewText: I bought this item using my own funds.It has a cute color. It also has the removal mesh bag for sponges or cotton balls. The clear pocket in the lid can house smaller eye pencils, lipstick, eyeshadows, jewelry, hair ties, hair clips or other items. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for ALL Travel Toiletries & Essentials!
reviews.reviewText: This travel bag is even better than I expected! I travel quite a bit for work and this bag can hold ALL of my travel necessities. For me, the necessities include oil cleanser, normal cleanser, toner, exfoliant, essence, moisturizer, sun screen, foundation/skin tint, travel shampoo/conditioner, leave in conditioner, travel mousse, plus any jewelry I plan to wear, hair ties, a razor, bandaids, retainer case, AND a small container of medication. The zipper is high quality and the bag appears to be pretty water resistant.The only downside worth mentioning, although this may not matter to most, is the vertical style. This is the first bag I've owned that is vertical where all bottles can sit upright. This is great in terms keeping everything upright and for saving space horizontally, but if you plan to have this bag inside a backpack or any other bag, keep in mind you wont be able to put much on top of it - for example, placed inside my backpack, I can only put a few things next to it and nothing on top of it. I am still giving a 5-star rating because this is something I don't mind and others probably expect buying a bag that is cylindrical in shape. Overall, this is a great "grab-and-go" travel bag that holds a ton! Definitely recommend! *photos pending

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A smaller, taller case that hold a lot.
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had a small simple black vegan leather makeup case for years, and it’s served me well, tucking easily into a drawer or suitcase, taking up very little room. Alas, it’s finally starting to fall apart. Been looking for a replacement, but it’s quite hard to find a small one anymore. Most are much bigger than I need, designed to hold a Kardashian amount of makeup.I finally found this one by Icramsy. While it's larger than my old one, it’s smaller than most others out there. It’s also more of a vertical orientation than I’m used to. Before, I’d just throw the makeup in the old case, horizontally on top of each other, and then fish it out as I needed it. After travel, it’d usually get all jumbled up. This new Icramsy makeup case is much more organized, with several elasticized pouches all around the interior edge. So now I can place mascaras and eyeliners vertically in one pouch, blush in another, foundation in another, all neatly standing up on end. They are much more accessible and easy to grab. Inside the lid, there’s also a handy clear pouch with a snap, perfect for small things like nail scissors, foam applicators and hair bands. There’s also a mesh pouch on a tether. Not sure what I’ll use that for, but it’s a nice extra.Because of its bigger size, I can even add in more products - tall sprays like deodorant, perfume and mousse. It’s more than just a makeup case, but a toiletry one, to boot. The zipper is situated at about 3/5th of the way up the case, which is something new to get used to. On the plus side, it allows the tops of the tubes to show and be easier to grab when the case is flipped open.I ordered the case in black. The outer material is not very luxe, more like a thin nylon dopp kit rather than a leather look. The red interior is actually a nice contrast and makes the dark cosmetic containers easy to spot.While I was initially disappointed it was so tall, I’m now seeing it as a positive and enjoying the extra storage space. Overall I’m quite happy with it.
